comment_data.body:
Well after ad4bc2d we can omit all this tui argument passing and do the same thing - setup autocmd on `UIEnter` so it will start listening on our original pipe and close listener on auto-generated address:
```
 // Restore --listen address on UIEnter (after old server exits).
    MAXSIZE_TEMP_DICT(listen_opts, 2);
    PUT_C(listen_opts, "once", BOOLEAN_OBJ(true));
    PUT_C(listen_opts, "command", CSTR_AS_OBJ(
      "call serverstart(g:_nvim_listen)"
      " | for s in serverlist()"
      " | if s !=# g:_nvim_listen"
      " | call serverstop(s)"
      " | endif"
      " | endfor"));
    MAXSIZE_TEMP_ARRAY(listen_autocmd_args, 2);
    ADD_C(listen_autocmd_args, CSTR_AS_OBJ("UIEnter"));
    ADD_C(listen_autocmd_args, DICT_OBJ(listen_opts));
    rpc_send_call(channel->id, "nvim_create_autocmd", listen_autocmd_args,
                  &result_mem, &err);
```
Though we will setup `_nvim_listen`:
```
// Store --listen address on new server.
    MAXSIZE_TEMP_ARRAY(setvar_args, 2);
    ADD_C(setvar_args, CSTR_AS_OBJ("_nvim_listen"));
    ADD_C(setvar_args, CSTR_AS_OBJ(listen_arg));
    rpc_send_call(channel->id, "nvim_set_var", setvar_args, &result_mem, &err);
```

maybe there is a way to simplify this further

